title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.1: IMMUNIZATION

description.narrative: Output 1.1: National routine immunization reaches each and every child, coverage is sustained at more than 85% as measured by Penta 3 and SIAs reach >90% coverage of the target population including hard-to-reach areas, which contributes to Immunization, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By 2019, children, adolescents and women, especially in the most vulnerable and hard-to-reach areas, including those in emergencies, utilize high impact evidence-based quality essential health services.

title.narrative: Output 1.1: National routine immunization reaches each and every child, coverage is sustained at more than 85% as measured byPenta 3 and SIAs reach >90% coverage of the target population including hard-to-reach areas

description.narrative: By October 2019, routine immunization coverage as measured by DPT3 was 72% (annual target 85%), with at least 13 out of the 15 counties achieving greater than 80% coverage. Coverage of the May Integrated Polio Campaign was 99% (938,025 children of the targeted 945,464 children aged 0–59 months vaccinated). Dropout between DPT1 and DPT3 was 7% (annual target <8%). There were zero months of stockouts at national and regional levels for the measles vaccine and other vaccines, including Gavi-supported vaccines. | Status:Met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
